sections_as_in_manuscript: Development of a novel strategy to knockout Tet1/2/3 alleles by CRISPR/Cas9
TET1 and TET2, but not TET3, are required for somatic lineage commitment
The combined loss of TET1 and TET2 enhances ESC self-renewal
Loss of TETs does not affect transitions from na√Øve to formative or primed pluripotency
TET-deficient cells efficiently acquire germline markers without requiring inductive cytokines
Transcriptional changes indicate efficient germline differentiation of TET-deficient cells
TET-deficient PGCLCs show precocious expression of late germline markers
Expression of PGC TFs indicates accelerated germline entry in TET-deficient cells
TET-deficient PGCLCs express a transcriptional profile characteristic of a later developmental stage in vivo
